  Our present legal system has some serious flaws with it. My friend recently was called for jury duty.  He was a juror in a sexual harrasment case.  He clearly felt that the womans was wrong in claiming sexual harassment, especially given that she intitiated much of the alleged harassment (something along the lines of: I can make any man orgasm in under 6 minutes(I laughed at this point, commenting that that isn't that much of an accomplishment)).  But since the other jurors felt bad for her, he went along with them and they recommended an award of $60,000 to her.  All because he didn't want to argue the point and delay the trial, or to result in a hung jury.  Also look at the fact that the people on juries are usually the people that couldn't find a good enough excuse not to serve on them. (Though if I get called I actually would go, it is my duty, tedious though it may be)<br>
